import React from 'react';

class NavBar extends React.Component {
    render() {
        return <head>
            <title>{this.props.title}</title>
            <script src="../Content/Dependencies/knockout-min.js"></script>
            <link rel="stylesheet" href="../Content/Dependencies/notyf.min.css"/>
            <script src="../Content/Dependencies/notyf.min.js"></script>
            <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/icon?family=Material+Icons"/>
            <script
                src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js"
                integrity="sha256-/xUj+3OJU5yExlq6GSYGSHk7tPXikynS7ogEvDej/m4="
                crossOrigin="anonymous"></script>
            <link rel="stylesheet" href="../Content/index.css"/>
            <link rel="stylesheet" href="../Content/colors.css"/>
            <script src="../Content/js.js"></script>
            <script src="../Content/CsvExport.js"></script>
            <script src="../Content/Dependencies/knockout-fast-foreach-lib.js"></script>
            <script src="../Content/Dependencies/knockout.autocomplete.js"></script>
            <script src="../Content/Dependencies/quill.min.js"></script>
            <link rel="stylesheet" href="../Content/Dependencies/quill.snow.css"/>
            <script src="../Content/Dependencies/chart.min.js"></script>
        </head>
    }
}

export default NavBar;
